{"word":"Ἀβιά","slug":"Ἀβιά","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ἀβιά, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Heb.\">Heb.</a>] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ indecl.\">indecl.</a> <b><i>Abijah</i><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> son of Rehoboam (<a href='B:130 3:10'>1 Chronicles 3:10</a>), in genealogy of <b><a href='B:470 1:7'>Mt 1:7</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> founder of a class of priests (<a href='B:130 24:10'>1 Chronicles 24:10</a>) to which Zacharias belonged <b><a href='B:490 1:5'>Lk 1:5</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἅβελ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἀβιαθάρ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}